I’m 29, and these are 3 things I started for my skin last year that help me stay low-maintenance while still keeping it healthy, resilient, and calm.

✨Photofacials – Such a great option if you have sensitive skin. They help reduce redness, boost collagen, and improve skin texture over time. Zero downtime, and they’ve genuinely helped my skin feel more stable.

✨Collagen supplements – A few I really trust: @wellbeing.nutrition @trunativ @neocell @hkvitals 

Collagen has made a noticeable difference in how firm and plump my skin feels. It’s also great for joints, hair, and nails so it’s a full-body win.

✨Laser Hair Reduction – I’ve never shaved my face or done my brows (my hair’s always been fine and light), and overall I don’t have much body hair either. But I used to wax my arms and half legs, laser has been such a game changer for that. It’s just made my routine so much simpler.

Let me know if you have any questions on any of these 💬✨

If you’ve been following me for a while, you already know I don’t believe in restricting myself. I love indulging in the things I enjoy, but I’m always on the lookout for healthier swaps that actually taste good. 😋✨

So here’s Part 1 of the regular grocery swaps I’ve made in my life:

🍪 Sweet cravings? I reach for the cookies or chocolate fudges from Cinnamon Kitchen. Minimal ingredients, no refined sugar, lots of gluten-free & vegan options.

🥔 Salty snack urge? I’m not a huge chip person, but when I want something crunchy, Popeas Puffs are perfect. I genuinely love all their flavours!

🍫 If you’re not acne-prone, Get-A-Whey’s Belgian Chocolate Ice Cream is SO good and comes with added protein.

🍞 Bread swaps: No maida for me on a regular basis. I alternate between whole wheat, ragi, or sourdough breads (especially wheat sourdough).

🍚Shirataki noodles or rice are my go-to. Super low calorie, and can be used in so many ways. 

🌱Pasta: I love the ones from Dona Pastatia minimal ingredients, no maida.

🥤 Quick protein: Epigamia Turbo Protein Milkshake is a regular in my fridge.

🍦 Sugar-free ice cream: You already know I’m obsessed with Minus 30: vegan + sugar-free = love.

🍝 Gluten-free noodles: Try Naturally Yours, great texture and very filling.

🍹 Gut health? Swap your sodas with Kombucha!

I didn’t pay full price for most of it🙈

📍 If you’re planning a Euro trip soon, don’t miss these pharmacy stops:

✨ Citypharma – Paris, France
Crowded? Yes. 
Worth it? Absolutely. Avène, Bioderma, Nuxe, La Roche-Posay... all for way less.

✨ Farmacia del Corso – Rome, Italy
A local gem. Amazing Italian dermo brands, beauty supplements, and the sweetest staff ever.

✨ El Corte Inglés Pharmacy – Barcelona, Spain

So yes, I went a little wild... but strategically. 😏

3 months into marriage… after 15 years of dating🩷. Sreeja’s bit 

People always say, “It must feel the same, you married your best friend.”

And yes, it is beautiful… but let me be real: a lot changes.

From syncing bathroom schedules to aligning on savings, spending habits, and even how we share space… marriage brings a new kind of intimacy.

It’s not always butterflies: it’s shared responsibilities, silent understandings, unspoken teamwork.

Love isn’t just about the big gestures, it’s in the everyday effort.
And after 15 years of dating + 3 months of being married, I’ve learned this:
Love is a choice you make, over and over again even on the days it’s not easy.

If you’re watching this and thinking about marriage, here’s a little big-sister advice:

Don’t do it because it’s the “next step” or because others are doing it.
Do it only when you’re sure you’re ready to build a life with someone, not just beside them.

Here’s to the next chapter: slow, imperfect, but full of heart. 💛

Okay, first things first, these photos aren’t from a professional camera😅

I’m still waiting on the official wedding photos and videos, so everything you’re seeing here is just taken on my phone, mostly in natural light. So if some details aren’t super visible, that’s why but I still wanted to share everything because so many of you had asked 🫶

Outfit 1: Welcome Dinner
I wanted something whimsical but rewearable. I knew it had to be western and comfortable. I saw this dress by @varunnidhika and instantly loved it🤍
💸: RS 1,98,000

Outfit 2: Mehendi Carnival
I knew I didn’t want to go with pinks or purples. I wanted something green, fun, and flowy. After a LOT of searching, I found this at @anantamofficial : it’s by a Calcutta-based designer named Anshul Jain.
💸: RS 75,000

Outfit 3: Sangeet
I’m not a full sequin girl but I still wanted that glam moment. Tried so many things that looked great but felt terrible. Ended up with this @varunnidhika look: no can-can, super lightweight, didn’t scratch, and looked amazing on stage ✨
💸: RS 3,75,000

Outfit 4: Haldi
This was the very first outfit I finalised. I wanted something soft, minimal, and I knew I’d be wearing my nani’s wedding set so I built the whole look around that. The moment I saw the blouse, I just knew. @plumtin_motif 
💸: RS 1,26,000

Outfit 5: Wedding
I always thought I’d be a pastel bride until I tried on a few looks and realised darker colours suit me way more. I found this outfit at @plumtin_motif (Chandigarh) in October. Kept exploring other options, but my heart just kept coming back to this one. The colour, the blouse, the way it felt: it was the one.
💸: RS 2,80,000 

And just a quick note: I planned this wedding for over a year and a half, and I really took my time choosing every outfit. I’m someone who can’t be rushed into big decisions (especially the kind you’re photographed in forever 😅).

There are so many incredible designers and options out there and they don’t all have to be big names. Everyone’s budget, style, and comfort is different. 

Take inspiration, explore a little, but choose what actually feels like you.
